objects.name: Agriculture
objects.description: Private entities specialized in the growth, culture, transport and transformation of plants or livestock for food.

objects.name: Culture
objects.description: Private and public entities involved in creating, producting, and distributing goods and services that are cultural in nature, or protecting it.
Sector Culture is a subsector of Culture and entertainment

objects.name: Sports
objects.description: Private and public entities involved in producing, organizing, promoting  goods and services associated with sports.
Sector Sports is a subsector of Culture and entertainment

objects.name: Movies industry
objects.description: Private and public entities involved in filmmaking.
Sector Movies industry is a subsector of Culture and entertainment

objects.name: Education and research
objects.description: Public or private entities operating to facilitate learning and acquiring knowledge and skills and all research activities.

objects.name: Universities
objects.description: Institutions delivering high level education and research sanctionned by academic degrees.
Sector Universities is a subsector of Education and research

objects.name: Schools
objects.description: Primary and secondary schools or equivalent.
Sector Schools is a subsector of Education and research

objects.name: Think tanks
objects.description: Research institute/center and organization which performs research concerning mostly social sciences.
Sector Think tanks is a subsector of Education and research

objects.name: Scientific research centers & Laboratories
objects.description: Research institute and laboratories wich performs research concerning scientific topics.
Sector Scientific research centers & Laboratories is a subsector of Education and research

objects.name: Energy
objects.description: Public and private entities operating to extract, store, transport and process fuel, entities managing energy plants and energy storage and distribution and entities managing fuel waste.

objects.name: Electricity
objects.description: Public or private entities involved in the storage, transport and distribution of electricity to end customers.
Sector Electricity is a subsector of Energy

objects.name: Nuclear
objects.description: Civilian entities involved in the extraction and transport of nuclear fuel, civilian entities operating nuclear plants for civilian purposes, entities processing nuclear waste.
Sector Nuclear is a subsector of Energy

objects.name: Gas
objects.description: Public or private entities involved in exploration, extraction, refining, transporting and marketing of natural gas products.
Sector Gas is a subsector of Energy

objects.name: Oil
objects.description: The oil industry includes the global processes of exploration, extraction, refining, transporting (often by oil tankers and pipelines), and marketing of petroleum products.
Sector Oil is a subsector of Energy

objects.name: Renewable energies
objects.description: Public and private entities involved in the production of electricity based on renewable ressources.
Sector Renewable energies is a subsector of Energy

objects.name: Aviation
objects.description: All entities transporting people or goods by plane, managing or exploiting airports and structures, trafic authorities and plane manufacturers. Includes all civilian space activities.
Sector Aviation is a subsector of Transport

objects.name: Rail
objects.description: Public and private entities managing rail infrastructures, rail transportation, exploiting intelligent rail transport systems and the rail industry
Sector Rail is a subsector of Transport

objects.name: Maritime
objects.description: All entities transporting people or good by naval means, managing or exploiting naval structures (ports), naval manufactures and trafic authorities.
Sector Maritime is a subsector of Transport

objects.name: Road
objects.description: Public and private entities managing road infrastructures, road transportation, exploiting intelligent transport systems and the automotive industry.
Sector Road is a subsector of Transport

objects.name: Defense
objects.description: Public and private organizations involved in the production of weapons, planning and conducting military operations.

objects.name: Ministry of defense
objects.description: Includes the military and all defense related-space activities.
Sector Ministry of defense is a subsector of Defense

objects.name: Defense contractors
objects.description: Private entities providing products or services in support of military or intelligence capacities.
Sector Defense contractors is a subsector of Defense

objects.name: Research and development
objects.description: R&D for defense or military purposes.
Sector Research and development is a subsector of Defense

objects.name: Banking institutions
objects.description: Includes Central Banks.
Sector Banking institutions is a subsector of Banking and finance
Sector Financial organizations is a subsector of Banking and finance
Sector Insurance services is a subsector of Banking and finance
Sector Market infrastructures is a subsector of Banking and finance

objects.name: Diplomacy
objects.description: Public or private entities which are actors of or involved in international relations activities.

objects.name: Ministries of foreign affairs
objects.description: Governmental entities in charge of the diplomatic actions.
Sector Ministries of foreign affairs is a subsector of Diplomacy

objects.name: Specialized think tanks
objects.description: Research institutes specialized in policy and advocacy on diplomatic subjects.
Sector Specialized think tanks is a subsector of Diplomacy

objects.name: Intergovernmental organizations (IGOs)
objects.description: International organizations made up primarily of sovereign states and involved in setting international agendas and policies.
Sector Intergovernmental organizations (IGOs) is a subsector of Diplomacy

objects.name: Government and administrations
objects.description: Civilian administrations or institutions, including parliamentary institutions and local administrations.

objects.name: Central administration and Ministries
objects.description: Exclude Ministries of Foreign Affairs and Ministries of Defense
Sector Central administration and Ministries is a subsector of Government and administrations

objects.name: Local administrations
objects.description: Public administrations administring a local territory under the global authority of a central governement.
Sector Local administrations is a subsector of Government and administrations

objects.name: Parliamentary chambers
objects.description: Legislative bodies of a governement.
Sector Parliamentary chambers is a subsector of Government and administrations

objects.name: Health
objects.description: Public and private entities involved in all services and manufacturing of good related to public health.

objects.name: Healthcare services
objects.description: Hospital and other direct medical practice activities.
Sector Healthcare services is a subsector of Health

objects.name: Pharmacy and drugs manufacturing
objects.description: Public and private entities involved in producing medicinal products and drugs.
Sector Pharmacy and drugs manufacturing is a subsector of Health

objects.name: Healthcare research
objects.description: Public and private research centers focusing on Health improvement.
Sector Healthcare research is a subsector of Health

objects.name: Hospitality
objects.description: Private structures involved in receiving and entertaining people.
Sector Hotels is a subsector of Hospitality
Sector Restaurants is a subsector of Hospitality

objects.name: Tourism industry
objects.description: All private entities in the tourism industry except for transportations companies.
Sector Tourism industry is a subsector of Hospitality

objects.name: Technologies
objects.description: Private entities related to the research, development, manufacturing and distribution of electronics, softwares, computers and products related to information technologies.
Sector High-tech is a subsector of Technologies
Sector Gaming is a subsector of Technologies

objects.name: Manufacturing
objects.description: Private entities specialized in the transformation of raw materials into manufactured goods, except for transportation and technologies.
Sector Industry is a subsector of Manufacturing
Sector Construction is a subsector of Manufacturing

objects.name: Retail
objects.description: Private entities transporting and selling consumer goods and services to customers through multiple channels of distribution to earn a profit.

objects.name: Telecommunications
objects.description: Private and public entities involved in the production, transportand dissemination of information and communication signals.
Sector Communication service providers is a subsector of Telecommunications
Sector Hosting service provider is a subsector of Telecommunications
Sector IXPs is a subsector of Telecommunications
Sector DNS services is a subsector of Telecommunications

objects.name: Medias and audiovisual
objects.description: Communication outlets and people working in these outlets used to deliver information by print, broadcast or Internet.
Sector Medias and audiovisual is a subsector of Telecommunications

objects.name: Consulting
objects.description: Private organism providing expert advice in a specific field to external entities.
Sector Legal consulting is a subsector of Consulting
Sector IT consulting is a subsector of Consulting
Sector Engineering consulting is a subsector of Consulting

objects.name: Mining
objects.description: All activities related to the extraction, transport and sell of mineral and metal reserves.

objects.name: Water
objects.description: All public and private structures involved in the collection, transport and distribution of water for consumption purposes.

objects.name: Civil society
objects.description: Non-governemental entities, or individuals independant of governements, which may be linked by interests or activities aiming at promoting the interests and the will of citizens.

objects.name: Non governmental organizations
objects.description: NGOs
Sector Non governmental organizations is a subsector of Civil society
Sector Citizens is a subsector of Civil society
Sector Political organizations is a subsector of Civil society
Sector Dissidents is a subsector of Civil society
